This paper discusses the development and evaluation of a transactional web archive solution, which falls under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of the Memento protocol for accessing archived web content, which is relevant to web archiving (cs.WEB) and potentially also to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper touches on issues related to web security and compliance, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
